Muzilikazi Manyike. Chris Ricco/BackpagePix JOHANNESBURG - Former SA Schools captain Muzi Manyike has been confirmed dead after going missing last November. The Randfontein police officially opened a missing person's docket when Manyike's family became concerned over a lack of contact. CCTV footage reportedly showed Manyike leaving a car in Pretoria North before disappearing. READ: Former SA Schools captain Muzi Manyike reported missing The desperate search continued for weeks, but his family has now confirmed his passing after identifying his remains on Monday. According to mortuary records, Manyike’s body was discovered near the R101 in Hammanskraal north of Pretoria. The cause of death remains unknown at this point.